COVID in Brazil

A Date Visualisation of COVID in Brazil.

Xinran Liu true
09-11-2021

Introduction

Covid-19 has already left a trail of death and despair in Brazil, one of the worst in the world. Now, a year into the pandemic, the country is setting another wrenching record.

No other nation that experienced such a major outbreak is still grappling with record-setting death tolls and a health care system on the brink of collapse. Many other hard-hit nations are, instead, taking tentative steps toward a semblance of normalcy.

But Brazil is battling a more contagious variant that has trampled one major city and is spreading to others, even as Brazilians toss away precautionary measures that could keep them safe.

Data Description

The data in this Blog is from Our World in Data1.

The data is available in csv, xlsxformat. Im useing csv format for this blog post.

The main dataset is of dimensions 112659, 62, whereas the mainly used date for Brazil alone is 550, 13.

Analysis & Findings

Carform Cases and Death Number

Figure 1: The Growth of Carform Cases and Death Number in Brazil

The Figure1 represents the dynamics of the number of confirmed COVID diagnoses and the number of deaths due to New Coronavirus in Mexico from February 26, 2020 to August 27, 2021. By looking at the data in the graph, wonders what is the death rate of the New Coronavirus epidemic in Brazil?

The world average COVID death rate is 2.78 % and the average COVID death rate of Brazil is 3.32%, Which is 1.19 times of the world average.

The Trend of Daily Death Number

Figure 2: The Trend of Daily Case Number

According to the Figure2, We can see that although the situation in March 2021 is still relatively stable, the most deaths are all concentrated in April, and all deaths are greater than 3500. There are even two days where the number of deaths is greater than 4000.

The Trend of People Getting Vaccin

Figure 3: The Trend of People Get Vaccin

Vaccination has been highly recommended as one of the effective ways to fight the COVID virus.

In Figure3, in Brazil, vaccination is being implemented from the beginning of 2021 and the vaccination rate is very fast, with the blue part being the total vaccination, the pink part being the first dose of vaccine and the green part being the full dose.

The newest COVID vaccin rate in Brazil is 27.65% and the average COVID vaccin rate in the world is 46.1%, Which is 66.74% higher than the vaccin rate in Brazil.
